    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Add your <strong>chicken </strong>to a clean chopping board</p><p>Cover with <strong>cling film </strong>and bash with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> until flattened to approx. 1cm thickness</p><p>Sprinkle each side with a little of your<strong> five-spice mix</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-five-spice-chicken-with-cauliflower-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>flattened chicken</strong> to the pan and cook for 5-6 min on each side or until browned and cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>chicken breast</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 5? Use two pans!</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-five-spice-chicken-with-cauliflower-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Top, tail and slice your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> into discs on the diagonal (no need to peel!)</p><p>Wash your <strong>spring greens</strong> then pat it dry with kitchen paper, then rip the leaves off your <strong>spring greens</strong>, discard the tough stalks, then layer the leaves over each other, roll them up and slice into thin strips</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced carrot</strong> to a heatproof bowl, then cover with <strong>cling film</strong> and pierce a few holes in the top with a fork and put the bowl in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 2-3 min or until slightly softened</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-five-spice-chicken-with-cauliflower-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong> thinly</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Combine your <strong>hoisin sauce</strong> with your<strong> BBQ sauce</strong>,<strong> tomato paste</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and <strong>remaining five-spice mix</strong> in a small bowl</p><p>Add 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[65ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [90ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and 1/2 tsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [3/4 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [1 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong> and stir it all together until completely combined \u2013 this is your<strong> sauce mix</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-five-spice-chicken-with-cauliflower-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a pot with a matching lid over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>cauliflower rice</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook, stirring often, for 3-4 min or until warmed through</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p><p>Tip: Add a splash of water if it's looking a little dry!</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-five-spice-chicken-with-cauliflower-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once cooked, transfer the chicken to a plate and keep warm, reserve the pan</p><p>Return the pan to a medium-high heat with your <strong>toasted sesame oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>carrot discs</strong> (Tip: Be careful not to tip in any excess water from the bowl!) and the <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>spring greens</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Cook for 3-4 min or until tender with a bite \u2013 this is your <strong>sesame veg</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-five-spice-chicken-with-cauliflower-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the veg is cooking, put the sauce mix in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 1-2 min or until hot and slightly thickened \u2013 this is your <strong>Chinese-style five-spice bbq sauce</strong></p><p>Slice the <strong>chicken breast[s]</strong> thinly</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chinese-style-five-spice-chicken-with-cauliflower-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> sliced chicken breast</strong> with the <strong>cauliflower rice</strong> and <strong>sesame veg</strong> to the side</p><p>Drizzle the <strong>Chinese-style five-spice bbq sauce</strong> over the chicken and garnish with the <strong>sliced spring onion</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
